            <fr:title text="Negatively univalent deductive system">Negatively univalent deductive system</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A <fr:link href="jms-0048.xml" title="Deductive system" addr="jms-0048" type="local">deductive system</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> is called <fr:em>negatively univalent</fr:em> when for any negative <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\in \mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex>, the type of negative objects <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B\in \mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> equipped with a <fr:link href="jms-004R.xml" title="Thunkably and linearly invertible maps" addr="jms-004R" type="local">linearly invertible</fr:link> <fr:link href="jms-004A.xml" title="Linear and thunkable maps" addr="jms-004A" type="local">linear</fr:link> map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f:B\vdash  A]]></fr:tex> is contractible.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
